net.proteusframework.cms.controller

Class CmsRequest<T extends PageElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.cms.controller.CmsRequest<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the request datasource.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.proteusframework.internet.http.Request

    public final class CmsRequest<T extends PageElement>
extends Object
implements net.proteusframework.internet.http.Request
    Defines a Request for content in the CMS framework.

    This object is valid only for the current request. Do not store this object as it is no longer valid after the request is complete.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

      • getInputStream

        public InputStream getInputStream()
        Get the request data as in InputStream.

        Either getInputStream() or getReader() may be called, but not both.

        The data may already be consumed which can cause an error to be generated in some cases. Be careful mixing calls to get the request body and get parameters especially if the content type is either application/x-www-form-urlencoded or multipart/form-data.

      • isInRequestPath

        public boolean isInRequestPath(PageElement... children)
        Return true if the current element and any specified children are in the request path.

        Request path refers to an optional page element path specified in the URL. This usually looks something like /path/FdxbQVIpg1316,bx731,cb67755. The last element in the path is referred to as the request target or request path target.

        This means that the current element or the last optionally specified child element should be the target OR a child of the targeted page element.
        Parameters:
        children - the children.
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • isPartial

        public boolean isPartial()
        Return true if request is partial.

        This is used to indicate that a path within a hierarchical PageElement is being targeted and not the entire PageElement.

        Specified by:
        isPartial in interface net.proteusframework.internet.http.Request
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • isRequestPathAncestor

        public boolean isRequestPathAncestor(PageElement... children)
        Return true if the current element is an ancestor of the request path target.

        Request path refers to an optional page element path specified in the URL. This usually looks something like /path/FdxbQVIpg1316,bx731, cb67755. The last element in the path is referred to as the request target or request path target.

        This means that the current element, getPageElement(), or the last optionally specified child element should be the ancestor of the request target.
        Parameters:
        children - optional children to append to the path used in the comparison.
        Returns:
        true or false.

      • isRequestTarget

        public boolean isRequestTarget(PageElement... children)
        Return true if the request path target is the current element or the last optionally specified child element.

        Note that this will be false for a Page level request.

        Parameters:
        children - optional children to append to the path that is checked.
        Returns:
        true or false;

      • setUserLocale

        public void setUserLocale(Locale locale)
        Set the user locale. This is the default locale for the page request. Setting this will override any content negotiation for the locale. If the user has cookies enabled, then the locale will be the preferred locale for future content negotiation.
        Specified by:
        setUserLocale in interface net.proteusframework.internet.http.Request
        Parameters:
        locale - the locale. If null, the locale is negotiated.
